<HEADLINE>
DEVLIN ACCEPTS 1-YEAR PACT 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By STEVE SCHOENFELD  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   TEMPE, ARIZ. - Center Mike Devlin has agreed to terms with the
Cardinals on a one-year deal.
</P>
<P>
   Devlin, who has been with the the team for three seasons, is
expected to sign today. Terms of the deal were not disclosed, but
it is believed to be worth $400,000.
</P>
<P>
   Also, wide receiver Chad Carpenter accepted the team's one-year
tender offer.
</P>
<P>
   Devlin, a sixth-year pro, started for the Cardinals in 1996 and
'97 and played behind Aaron Graham last season.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's good to be wanted, and they wanted me,'' Devlin said.
``It was clear to me I can help this team even if it's a backup
role. I think this is a good place to be.'' &QL; 
Briefly &QL; 
Agent Leigh Steinberg said he doesn't expect negotiations between
his newest client, free-agent linebacker Jamir Miller, and the
Cardinals to intensify until after the April 17 draft because the
team is focused on the draft. The Cardinals have only $2 million
left under their $57.3 million salary cap for next season.
</P>
<P>
   ``This will be an interesting cap-o-nomic case,'' Steinberg
said.
</P>
<P>
   Starting quarterback Jake Plummer spent Monday being
photographed at Papago Park for the cover shot of ``Sport''
magazine's July issue. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
