</P>
<P>
   HOME &AMP; GARDENCHAIRS _ Give a designer or artist a plain chair
and ask him to do his thing. What do you get? Some wild and funky
creations, and it's all for a good cause. The annual Chairish the
Future, a fundraiser for the Metro Atlanta Food Bank, is April 25.
The chairs will be on display at Lenox Square April 19 before the
big auction. (Flanders, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   WILD-GEORGIA _ They're comng in now, the colorful and melodious
songbirds of spring and summer - the warblers, tanagers, vireos,
grosbeaks, hummingbirds - that spend the winter in Latin and South
America. For many, if not most, of these tiny neotropicals, it is
the end of an arduous trek that has included a non-stop flight over
the Gulf of Mexico. (Seabrook, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   LEEMAY-COLUMN _ Gardening columnist Lee May says he moves plants
around in his garden so much they should be on wheels. (May,
Atlanta Jourtnal-Constitution).WARNER-ON-
</P>
