<HEADLINE>
PRESENTATION PERSPECTIVES 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By ANITA MABANTE LEACH  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHOENIX- Here are some books that offer inspiration and
instruction for garnishing and presentation:
</P>
<P>
   _ ``The Book of Garnishes,'' by June Budgen (HP Books, $12).
</P>
<P>
   Garnishes that won't intimidate you are shown in step-by-step
photos that are a trademark of this series.
</P>
<P>
   - ``Garnishing and Decoration,'' by Rudolph Biller (Virtue,
$44.95).
</P>
<P>
   Chef Biller leads the reader through a dazzling repertoire of
garnishes and presentations.
</P>
<P>
   - ``The Artful Table,'' by Donna Gorman and Elizabeth Heyert
(William Morrow and Co., $25).
</P>
<P>
   A designer and photographer approach table settings through the
principles of design, for a beautiful set of photographs and
suggestions. All that's missing are the recipes. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
