<P>
   The New York Times News Service plans the following articles
from the Style section for use Sunday, April 11, and thereafter. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   CONDOM-DESIGNER (Undated) _ A condom confrontation is taking
place in federal court in Newark in an emotionally charged dispute
over the exquisite architecture of the prophylactic. At the heart
of the imbroglio is Dr. Alla Venkata Krishna Reddy, a surgeon
turned businessman and inventor, and a controversial figure in the
prophylactic world. Reddy's designs for condoms with built-in
bulges are an attempt to rethink the way condoms work. By Patricia
Leigh Brown. WITH PHOTO.
</P>
<P>
   BACHELOR-PARTIES (New York) _ The whole point of a bachelor
party used to be to lament the bridegroom's final night of freedom,
his last shot at nondivorceable infidelity. But today's bachelor
parties are strictly G-rated, like a spa night for the guys. By
Rick Marin.
</P>
<P>
   GIRL-GROUPS (New York) _ The Williamsburgh Ladies Club and other
new women's groups mix career support and beauty tips, inspired by
the girl-talk of ``The View.'' By Rachel Lehman-Haupt.
</P>
<P>
   STEIN-NITEOUT (New York) _ As the evening began, Taylor Stein,
dressed in a black and white form-fitting Gucci suit, went to find
her jacket. A furry white low-cut tank top she had on was drawing
too much attention from the young (and not so young) gentlemen
arriving Thursday night at Brown's, the new Upper East Side boite
where Ms. Stein is an owner. By Monqiue Yazigi. WITH PHOTO.
</P>
