<P>
   HINGSTON-SUICIDE (Wilton, Conn.) _ The Hingston family cannot
comprehend why 17-year-old Samuel Hingston took his own life.
Neither will they accept that his past in New Jersey _ where he was
known not only as a scholar-athlete but also as an accused
13-year-old rapist who was ultimately acquitted _ may have hounded
him to his grave. By Bob Duffy. (2 takes) (a and s coding)
</P>
