   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-NATO (Washington) _ The speaker of the Cypriot Parliament
says his mission to free three captive American soldiers failed
because of the heavy NATO bombing of Belgrade. Meanwhile, President
Clinton rejects ``half measures'' by Yugoslav President Slobodan
Milosevic to make peace. By GREG McDONALD.
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON (Philadelphia) _ Amid the Balkan fighting, President
Clinton tries to give his domestic agenda a little daylight with a
