 For Release SATURDAY AMs, April 10, 1999  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Boston Globe plans to move the following stories for use by
NYTimes News Service clients.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; For questions about stories, contact  &UR; Frank Perrotta  &LR; at the
Boston Globe,  &UR; 617-929-2597. &LR;  For individual purchase of graphics
or photos please call 212 556-4204 or -1927.
</P>
<P>
   All stories will bear the BOS designator.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; CONFLICT IN THE BALKANS &LR;   &UR; (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-NATO (Moscow) -- Until now, Russian President Boris N.
Yeltsin has said Russia would not allow itself to be dragged into
the conflict over Kosovo. Friday that message changed _ to maybe.
By David Filipov. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   YUGOSLAVIA (Tirana, Albania) _ Serbs and KLA battle along the
border with Albania; Pentagon cites reports that Serbs are herding
Kosovar women into a camp near the Albanian border; a Cypriot
effort to free three American soldiers fails. By Anne E. Kornblut
and Mary Leonard. 1400 words.
</P>
<P>
   WORKERS-DETAINED (Undated) _ Yugoslav forces detain two
Australian aid workers, underlining danger of doing good in bad
places. By David Beard. 450 words.
</P>
<P>
   BOSNIA-CLINTON (Washington) _ When Clinton sent the planes over
Serbia, he was hoping it would work as it did when he sent bombers
during the Bosnia crisis. But the two situations are wholly
different. By Michael Kranish. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   SERBS-CARS (Skopji, Macedonia) _ At the Macedonian border Serb
guards split a group of Albanians into two lines, allowing one to
pass, the other to return to Kosovo. By Charles. M. Sennott. 1000
words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   DOLE-ABORTION (Undated) _ Elizabeth Dole says Republicans must
recognize ``that good and honorable people disagree'' about the
issue and that the fight to repeal the constitutional right to
abortion is all but a lost cause. By Jill Zuckman. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; COMMENTARY (k) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ELLIS-COLUMN (Undated) --The tax consequences of commerce on the
Internet. By John Ellis.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Y2K-UTILITIES (Udnated) _ ``Major test'' of utility
communications systems is mostly a publicity stunt, but it does
present an opportunity to weigh utilities' Y2K preparations. By
Ross Kerber. 600 words.
</P>
<P>
   TOBACCO-SIGNS (Undated) _ As part of the tobacco settlement,
tobacco companies have to replace their pro-smoking billboards with
antismoking versions. Boston ad agency's antismoking campaign will
appear in 17 states. By Chris Reidy. 750 words.
</P>
<P>
   FLEET-SEVERANCE (Boston) _ Fleet issues severance package for
employees to be laid off as a result of the BankBoston acquisition.
By Lynnley Browning. 500 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SPORTS (s) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   GLF-MASTERS (Augusta, Ga.) _ By Michael Madden.
</P>
<P>
   BBA-REDSOX-RAYS (Tampa) _ By Gordon Edes.
</P>
<P>
   BKN-SIXERS-CELTICS (Boston) By Michael Holley.
</P>
<P>
   MCDONOUGH-COLUMN (Undated) _ By Will McDonough.
