</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    COX NEWS SERVICE BUSINESS BUDGET
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   These business stories for release Saturday, April 10, 1999, are
moving today to clients of the New York Times News Service.
</P>
<P>
   Stories are moving in the financial (f) category. Stories also
moving in lifestyle will be marked with (f, l).
</P>
<P>
   Separate budgets move daily with spot news, features, sports and
commentary.
</P>
<P>
   If you have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the
Cox News Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   MEXICO-COKE _ The Mexican government today is expected to
consider Coca-Cola's purchase of Cadbury brands. Coca-Cola would
meld its powerful brands with Cadbury's Dr Pepper, Canada Dry and
the Schweppes line of mixers. The French government also is
considering the acquisition. Coke's stock is up slightly. (Unger,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   AIRFARES _ ATLANTA _ Continental Airlines raised its leisure
fares 3 percent and its walkup fares 1 percent on Friday, signaling
the industry's third increase this year if competitors follow suit.
(Thurston, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   AT&AMP;T-BELLSOUTH _ ATLANTA _ AT&AMP;T Corp. is buying BellSouth
Corp.'s wireless operations in Honolulu for about $160 million.
(Clothier, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   COXCOMMUNICATIONS _ ATLANTA _ Cox Communications confirmed
Friday that it has renegotiated a contract that could give the
cable operator greater control of high-speed Internet provider At
Home.
</P>
<P>
   The Atlanta-based company's is seeking greater control of At
Home. What it really wants is to spur AT&AMP;T, which owns a
controlling stake in At Home, to sign up more cable subscribers to
use the Internet service of the Silicon Valley start up. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   METROJET _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ In July, US Airways will
start low-fare MetroJet service between PBIA and three cities in
the Northeast _ Hartford, Baltimore and Boston. (Pounds, Palm Beach
Post)
</P>
<P>
   Y2K-DRILL _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Florida Power &AMP; Light will
participate in Friday's nationwide utility Y2K readiness drill. The
utility will simulate the simultaneous breakdown of several primary
communication systems to figure out which backups to use in case of
a real problem. We'll look at the schedule of FPL's Y2K events.
(Spencer-Wendel, Palm Beach Post)
</P>
<P>
   TESTDRIVE-BLAZER _ A review of the Chevrolet Trail Blazer, a
specialized sport-utility (DeVault, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
WITH PHOTO.
</P>
