<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKC-PEPPERDINE-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
PEPPERDINE STARTS PRELIMINARY INTERVIEWS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CHRIS BRANAM  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Pepperdine athletic director John Watson has begun
preliminary interviews for the school's vacant head men's
basketball coach position.
</P>
<P>
   Watson has been out of the office this week, presumably
traveling to meet with out-of-town applicants for the job. Sources
indicate Don Meyer, the head coach at Lipscomb University in
Nashville, is a serious candidate.
</P>
<P>
   Randy Bennett, the top assistant this past season at Pepperdine
under former coach Lorenzo Romar, remains the leading contender for
the job. Other confirmed applicants are Biola head coach Dave
Holmquist, Rhode Island assistant Jim Harrick Jr., UC Santa Barbara
assistant Marty Wilson and UCLA assistants Michael Holton and Jim
Saia.
</P>
<P>
   Holmquist, 48, has coached at Biola, an NAIA school in La
Mirada, for 21 years. Biola was 29-8 last season and played for the
NAIA championship in 1982.
</P>
<P>
   ``I haven't heard anything yet,'' Holmquist said, adding he
hasn't had a formal interview with Watson.
</P>
<P>
   Romar resigned last month after three seasons to become the head
coach at Saint Louis University.
</P>
<P>
   Also: Jelani Gardner, a two-time All-West Coast Conference
basketball selection at Pepperdine, will participate in the Desert
Classic, a pre-NBA draft camp for college seniors.
</P>
<P>
   Gardner will be one of 36 players in Phoenix for the camp, which
will be scouted by all NBA teams in preparation for the draft,
which is June 30.
</P>
</TEXT>
