reported on Friday that they had found a rifle in woods behind the
doctor's house in Amherst, N.Y. While the finding of the rifle
appeared to be the biggest break in the case so far, it raised
questions among friends and relatives of Dr. Barnett Slepian as to
why local police and the FBI had not used high-technology methods
to locate the rifle much sooner. By Joseph Berger.
