<DOCNO> NYT19990409.0347 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-09 20:12 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A2693 &Cx1f; tad-z
u f &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-AIRFARES10-COX     04-09 0319
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-AIRFARES10-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Airlines hike fares, cite high demand
 &HT;    By Scott Thurston
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Big airlines moved Friday to raise fares for the third
time this year, emboldened by sky-high demand for seats and fearing
a rebound in fuel prices.
</P>
<P>
   The move boosted airline stocks, even though the increase could
crumble this weekend if all major carriers don't go along.
</P>
<P>
   Continental initiated the hike, which raises advance-purchase
fares 3 percent and unrestricted fares 1 percent.
</P>
<P>
   Delta, United and America West matched Friday.
</P>
<P>
   ``The decision is based on the enormous demand we have seen for
our product,'' Delta spokesman John Kennedy said. Industrywide,
traffic rose 4.9 percent in March against a 3.6 percent gain in
seat capacity.
</P>
<P>
   It probably won't be clear until Monday whether all major
carriers go along with the fare increase. If they don't, the
increase will likely be withdrawn.
</P>
<P>
   Rising crude oil prices could bring an end to low fuel costs
that boosted airline profits in 1998. It remains to be seen,
however, how high prices will rise, and big airlines have long-term
buying programs that cushion any immediate impact.
</P>
<P>
   The previous two fare hikes of 1999 raised business-type fares 3
percent, and leisure-type fares 7 percent. The increases came after
18 months of fare stability from mid-1997 through 1998.
</P>
<P>
   Northwest and US Airways did not immediately raise fares.
Northwest's reluctance to raise fares last year thwarted attempts
to implement increases in 1998, but the Minneapolis-based airline
has participated in the two fare hikes so far this year.
</P>
<P>
   In a weekly fare newsletter, BT Alex Brown Inc. said the average
business fare this week was up 6 percent over the same period last
year.
</P>
<P>
   The Associated Press contributed to this article.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
