   BACKPACKS (Seattle) _ In a spinal twist to education reform,
more and more kids are literally stooping to conquer. Youngsters,
some carrying half their body weight in overloaded backpacks, have
become unwitting beasts of burden, some physicians and
chiropractors say. Their message to kids and parents: Lighten up.
</P>
