<P>
   BC-MICROSOFT-WINDOWS-NYT (moved on Thurday, April 8)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Thurday, April 8,
about a shift in Microsoft's strategy for its operating systems
referred incorrectly in some copies to the company's initial
embrace of the Internet. It occurred in 1995, not 1997.
</P>
<P>
   BC-SCI-SLEEP-CAFFEINE-NYT (moved on Monday, March 15)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, March 15,
about sleep deprivation misspelled the surname of the chief of the
division of sleep and chronobiology at the University of
Pennsylvania Medical Center. He is Dr. David F. Dinges, not
Dingess.
</P>
