   FCC-KENNARD-PROFILE _ FCC Chairman William Kennard is
Washington's key official on issues of importance to the nation's
fastest growing industries. He has found himself politically hemmed
in from the start; relies to a surprising degree on Washington's
black power structure for support, and focuses much of his effort
on issues like minority ownership of TV stations and getting more
advertising for minority broadcasters. By Steven Labaton. WITH
PHOTO amd GRAPHIC.
</P>
